Arrian (<I>Anabasis</I>, 7.19.4)<!--</A>ARRIAN:ANABASIS--> speaks of the construction of triremes and other large boats at Babylon after Alexander's return to that city just before his death, but no punts are mentioned.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note18" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Diodorus_Siculus/19B*.html#ref18
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">18</A>
Eumenes was holding the citadel of Babylon, which he had captured in October, 318 (Tarn in <I>C. A. H.</I> 6.477).


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note19" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Diodorus_Siculus/19B*.html#ref19
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">19</A>
Pithon received Media in the distribution at Triparadeisus, but the satrap of Parthia is there called Philip
	<A HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Diodorus_Siculus/18B*.html#39.6
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,0,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">
(Book 18.39.6)</A>. As Diodorus' words suggest, Pithon's "<SPAN CLASS="whole">general</SPAN>&shy;ship" of the upper satrapies was by usurpation. For earlier projects of Pithon cp. <A HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Diodorus_Siculus/18B*.html#7
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,0,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">Book 18.7</A>.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note20" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Diodorus_Siculus/19B*.html#ref20
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">20</A>
He was originally appointed to this satrapy by Alexander


<A ID="p267x"></A>(Arrian, <I>Anabasis</I>, 6.30.2‑3)<!--</A>ARRIAN:ANABASIS--> and was continued in office by Perdiccas and by Antipater (Book 18.<A HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Diodorus_Siculus/18A*.html#3.3
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,0,WIDTH,175)"
