Literally, "with loose rein."


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note53" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Diodorus_Siculus/19B*.html#ref53
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">53</A>
This is some 2000 less than the total of the individual cavalry detachments listed in
	<A HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Diodorus_Siculus/19B*.html#29
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,5,WIDTH,140)"
onMouseOut="nd();">
chap. 29</A>.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note54" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Diodorus_Siculus/19B*.html#ref54
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">54</A>
The text is uncertain, but <SPAN LANG="el" CLASS="Greek">βάθος</SPAN>, "with a depth of 50 men," seems impossible. In
	<A HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Diodorus_Siculus/19B*.html#28.3
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,5,WIDTH,140)"
onMouseOut="nd();">
chap. 28.3
	</A>
we find six <SPAN CLASS="translit_Greek">eilae</SPAN> of 50 each and one of 300, but the latter is regarded as unusual.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note55" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Diodorus_Siculus/19B*.html#ref55
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">55</A>
The difference, if any, between the hypaspists and the other heavy armed foot soldiers is not clear. Tarn (<I>Hellenistic Military and Naval Developments</I>, 17) suggests that the "real distinction between the hypaspists and the phalanx was probably one of standing and recruitment; it was the difference between the Guards and the infantry of the line."


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note56" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Diodorus_Siculus/19B*.html#ref56
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">56</A>
To make these figures agree approximately with the totals of the separate units, we must either assume a considerable lacuna in chap. 27.6 or 28.1<!-- DON'T LINK -->, or else suppose that the light armed troops numbered about 18,000 and are included in the total; the 28,000 foot soldiers of Antigonus
	<A HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Diodorus_Siculus/19B*.html#27
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,5,WIDTH,140)"
onMouseOut="nd();">
(chap. 27.1)
	</A>
include only those capable of standing in the phalanx
	<A HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Diodorus_Siculus/19B*.html#29.3
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,5,WIDTH,140)"
onMouseOut="nd();">
(chap. 29.3)</A>.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note57" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Diodorus_Siculus/19B*.html#ref57
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">57</A>
The Tarentines were <SPAN CLASS="whole">cavalry&shy;men</SPAN> equipped with javelins. The connection with Tarentum is obscure, but Tarentine coins show such troops (A. Martin in
	<A HREF="
http://dagr.univ-tlse2.fr/feuilleter/tome_2/partie_1/page_774
	"TARGET="offsite"
onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,2,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">
Daremberg et Saglio, 2.770</A>).


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note58" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Diodorus_Siculus/19B*.html#ref58
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">58</A>
One must suppose that each of these brought an extra


<A ID="p309x"></A>mount to the battle, as did the Tarentines who followed Philopoemen
	<A HREF="
http://www.thelatinlibrary.com/livy/liv.35.shtml#28
	"TARGET="offsite"
onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,LatinRef2,WIDTH,190)"
onMouseOut="nd();">
(Livy, 35.28.8)</A>.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note59" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Diodorus_Siculus/19B*.html#ref59
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">59</A>
The outer end of the wing consisted of the 300 horse under Antigonus in line with the cavalry previously mentioned, an advance guard of three troops (of 50 men each?) from the personal retinue of Antigonus, and a rearguard of three similar troops plus 100 Tarentines (cp. <A HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Diodorus_Siculus/19B*.html#28.3
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,5,WIDTH,140)"
onMouseOut="nd();">chap. 28.3‑4</A>). The forces enumerated total 10,600 horse and 28,000 heavy infantry (cp. <A HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Diodorus_Siculus/19B*.html#27
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,5,WIDTH,140)"
onMouseOut="nd();">chap. 27.1</A>).


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note60" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Diodorus_Siculus/19B*.html#ref60
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">60</A>
None were less than sixty years of age
	<A HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Diodorus_Siculus/19B*.html#41.2
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,5,WIDTH,140)"
onMouseOut="nd();">
(chap. 41.2)</A>.


