onMouseOut="nd();">Book 18.7.4</A>.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note97" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Diodorus_Siculus/19B*.html#ref97
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">97</A>
Fischer suggests that some indication of the cavalry strength has been lost from the manuscripts at this point.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note98" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Diodorus_Siculus/19B*.html#ref98
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">98</A>
<I>i.e.</I> Meleager and Menoetas and their followers.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note99" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Diodorus_Siculus/19B*.html#ref99
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">99</A>
Cp. <A HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Diodorus_Siculus/18B*.html#39.5
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,0,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">Book 18.39.5‑7
	</A>
for the previous distribution.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note100" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Diodorus_Siculus/19B*.html#ref100
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">100</A>
Stasander, to whom Aria and Drangenê had been assigned by Antipater
	<A HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Diodorus_Siculus/18B*.html#39.6
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,0,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">
(Book 18.39.6)</A>, had supported Eumenes
	<A HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Diodorus_Siculus/19B*.html#14.7
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,5,WIDTH,140)"
onMouseOut="nd();">
(chap. 14.7)</A>.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note101" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Diodorus_Siculus/19B*.html#ref101
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">101</A>
Cp. <A HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Plutarch/Lives/Eumenes*.html#19.2
	"TARGET="Plutarch_E"
onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,Plutarch,WIDTH,PlutarchWidth)"
onMouseOut="nd();">Plutarch, <I>Eumenes</I>, 19.2</A>.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note102" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Diodorus_Siculus/19B*.html#ref102
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">102</A>
Peucestes never again played an important rôle, but he seems to have outlived Antigonus and to have retained, or regained, the favour of Demetrius (Phylarchus, <I>FGrH</I>, 81.12).


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note103" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Diodorus_Siculus/19B*.html#ref103
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">103</A>
Cp. chaps. <A HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Diodorus_Siculus/19B*.html#17.3
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,5,WIDTH,140)"
onMouseOut="nd();">17.3</A>,
	<A HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Diodorus_Siculus/19B*.html#18
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,5,WIDTH,140)"
onMouseOut="nd();">
18.1</A>.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note104" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Diodorus_Siculus/19B*.html#ref104
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">104</A>
For the golden vine that stood with the golden plane tree


<A ID="p363x"></A>in the chamber of the Persian king cp. <A HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Herodotus/7A*.html#27
	"TARGET="Herodotus_E"
onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,Herodotus,WIDTH,220)"
onMouseOut="nd();">Herodotus, 7.27</A>; Athenaeus, 12.514<SPAN CLASS="small">F</SPAN><!--</A>ATHENAEUS514-->.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note105" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Diodorus_Siculus/19B*.html#ref105
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">105</A>
Continued in
	<A HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Diodorus_Siculus/19C*.html#55
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,0,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">
chap. 55.1</A>.



	<HR CLASS="endnotes"><A ID="endnotes_T"></A>
	<H2>
Thayer's Note:
	</H2>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note:Syrian_writing" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Diodorus_Siculus/19B*.html#ref:Syrian_writing
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">a</A>
Ancient authors often write "Syrian" to mean, as here very likely, "Assyrian"; see for example
	<A HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Plutarch/Lives/Antony*.html#46.2
	"TARGET="Plutarch_E"
onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,Plutarch,WIDTH,PlutarchWidth)"
onMouseOut="nd();">
Plutarch, <I>Antony</I>, 46.2</A>.



